3Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dizzle","CreatedById":31588,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T07:24:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI didn\u0027t know I desperately needed this until I saw it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DBT85","CreatedById":114980,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T11:57:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMuch needed. The stock is far too small.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T14:05:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s up on CKAN now too.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darloth","CreatedById":4004,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T14:12:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt almost looks like you\u0027ve put more effort into the release forum post than went into the mod! (I know that\u0027s almost certainly not true even for a simple thing, but I found the post hilarious.)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThanks for this, as many others have said I didn\u0027t realize how much this annoyed me until you could change it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"biohazard15","CreatedById":91655,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T14:51:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENice job! (Although I won\u0027t use it, since I have CW\u002B from DMagic)\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T16:24:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darloth\u0022 data-cite=\u0022darloth\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIt almost looks like you\u0027ve put more effort into the release forum post than went into the mod! (I know that\u0027s almost certainly not true even for a simple thing, but I found the post hilarious.)\u003Cp\u003EThanks for this, as many others have said I didn\u0027t realize how much this annoyed me until you could change it.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf only that were true.... It was *surprisingly* difficult to get this to look right.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AppleDavidJeans","CreatedById":84275,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T18:13:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EFinally, no more cramped contracts window! Thanks for this simple but very useful solution! Btw, how many lines of code did this one take up?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEDIT: Also, will this work in all scenes?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DirtyFace83","CreatedById":131509,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T20:12:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESuper useful!!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T20:34:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AppleDavidJeans\u0022 data-cite=\u0022AppleDavidJeans\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EFinally, no more cramped contracts window! Thanks for this simple but very useful solution! Btw, how many lines of code did this one take up?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELet\u0027s see, with lazy counting including whitespace, comments, etc.... 102. Actual statement count is probably more like 4 or 5 dozen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AppleDavidJeans\u0022 data-cite=\u0022AppleDavidJeans\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EEDIT: Also, will this work in all scenes?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESupposed to, let me know if there\u0027s issues anywhere and I may have to up the lines of code by 3 or 4...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-12T16:17:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENew release - not any wider, but now with fewer NullReference errors (which weren\u0027t hurting anything, but they were red in the log and that\u0027s not nice). \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrossignol/WiderContractsApp/releases/tag/1.0.1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDownload it now\u003C/a\u003E!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWider Contracts App 1.0.1\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EFixed NullReference in log on startup.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tmbomber","CreatedById":104086,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-20T04:38:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAnybody noticing a memory leak with this???\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI installed a few mods, this being one of them, and I started crashing to desktop due to running out of memory every 20 minutes. I removed what I thought was the problem, but it didn\u0027t help. I finally installed GCMonitor to keep track of what was happening. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhat I noticed was that when I entered the VAB and clicked on the contract window my memory usage would shoot up at a rate of about a meg a second. (this was with nothing being worked on. VAB was empty at the time) If I closed the contract window memory usage would stabilize at where ever it was. Opening the contract window again would cause memory usage to increase.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI exited the game, removed WCA, restarted KSP, went back to the VAB, and opened the contract window. Memory usage remained stable.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-20T05:51:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve been using it for ages without apparent issue. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt really is a tiny mod though. I just re-read all the code looking for anything that could be a problem, and I didn\u0027t see anything obvious. I\u0027ll do some more in depth testing tomorrow.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-20T17:02:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve done a fair bit of testing (with gcmonitor), and I haven\u0027t really been able to tell a difference between with and without wider contracts app. The stock app is quite adept at leaking memory without me doing anything.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-28T03:22:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESadly, as of KSP 1.0 this mod is no longer possible as Squad has closed the holes in the Contracts App that allowed me to widen it. Complain to Squad if you\u0027d like to actually see more than 140 characters of contract text!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo I am now officially recommending \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/91034\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDMagic\u0027s Contracts Window \u002B\u003C/a\u003E as the alternative to Wider Contracts App. Long live Contracts Window \u002B.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-04-28T03:26:01Z\u0022 title=\u002204/28/2015 03:26  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EApril 28, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by nightingale\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-28T05:26:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EFalse alarm! With Unity, there is no such thing as a private object.... what a silly framework sometimes. But it allows me to continue to hack my widening shims into Squad\u0027s contracts app. I present...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EWIDER CONTRACTS APP FOR KSP 1.0! \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrossignol/WiderContractsApp/releases/tag/1.1.0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EDownload Now\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SwGustav","CreatedById":135958,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-28T09:31:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHey there, this version seems to offset Engineer\u0027s report - \u003Ca href=\u0022http://puu.sh/htJ56/ecba55dcb9.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Escreenshot\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou can pull it down (which is also required to expand list), but it\u0027s annoying.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-28T16:42:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYeah, the Engineer\u0027s report and Contracts app are sort of linked... Thought I\u0027d squashed all the cross-silliness issues, but guess it\u0027s not quite there yet. I\u0027ll get a fix out soon.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#C0C0C0;\u0022\u003E- - - Updated - - -\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENew version out, now with working Engineer\u0027s Report! \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrossignol/WiderContractsApp/releases/tag/1.1.1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDownload now\u003C/a\u003E!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWider Contracts App 1.1.1\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EFix Engineer\u0027s Report to display correctly (thanks SwGustav).\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ev0","CreatedById":116691,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-28T19:04:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EExcellent! Yours or DMagic\u0027s mod is necessary, but your\u0027s is simpler and that\u0027s how I like it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-02T05:18:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMost useless update ever! Works just as well as the old version, but necessary to make CKAN happy! \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrossignol/WiderContractsApp/releases/tag/1.1.2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDownload it now\u003C/a\u003E!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWider Contracts App 1.1.2\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00E2\u20AC\u00B9\u003C/strong\u003ERecompile for KSP 1.0.2 (for CKAN).\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ev0","CreatedById":116691,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-24T08:59:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027m getting frame rate drops when using only this mod.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMods Installed:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/116034-1-0-2-KerboKatz-SmallUtilities-V1-1-9-23-05-2015-Now-including-2-more-mods%21\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKerboKatz - SmallUtilities - FPSViewer\u003C/a\u003E (not the problem, I just used it to check my frame rate)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWider Contracts App\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHow to repeat:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDuring a career save, launch any craft. Note frame rate. Then, hover over contract menu on the stock toolbar. Note increase in frame rate!!\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou can notice this by looking at the FPSViewer, or by seeing the mission timer change colors from yellow to green if your frame rate is initially low enough.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImportant!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI \u003Cem\u003Ethink\u003C/em\u003E you get a larger increase the lower your graphics settings are (no AA, fastest render, etc.). With high settings, I wasn\u0027t seeing much of a difference between hovering over the contract menu and not. But when I turned the settings all the way down, I was getting \u002B15 fps! This does not happen with this mod uninstalled - I was getting the higher fps at all times with the stock contract menu.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EKerboKatz has a bunch of mods bundled with his SmallUtilities pack. Only FPSViewer is necessary, so you can delete the other plugins.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-05-24T09:01:40Z\u0022 title=\u002205/24/2015 09:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EMay 24, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by ev0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-24T14:33:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWow, those results seem counter-intuitive... I\u0027ll take a look in the next couple weeks, raised [\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrossignol/WiderContractsApp/issues/1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#1\u003C/a\u003E] on GitHub.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}